# OxidVault Coding Standards
- ALL code must pass 'cargo clippy' without warnings.
- Memory Security: Never use 'unsafe' blocks. Use 'zeroize::Zeroizing' for all cryptographic keys, passwords, and plaintexts on all exit paths.
- IPC Security: Never send raw secrets/passwörter via Tauri commands to the frontend. Use 'SecretEntryPublic' structures.
- Architecture: Strictly separate Business Logic (Rust) from UI (React). No business logic inside React states.
- Error Handling: No 'unwrap()' or 'expect()' in production code. Always use proper 'Result' matching.
- Documentation: Every architectural change, new IPC command, or security mitigation MUST be accurately documented in 'ARCHITECTURE.md' before completing the task.
